---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const pageData = {
    title: "Only 20% of Businesses Are Ready for Quantum Computing. Are You?",
    category: "Research Report",
    readTime: "10 min read",
    publishDate: "January 9, 2025",
   
    heroImage: "/company/c.jpg"
};
---
<Layout title={pageData.title}>
    <section class="bg-white">
        <!-- Hero Section -->
        <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-16 pb-12">
            <div class="text-center">
                <div class="inline-flex items-center bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 px-4 py-1 rounded-full mb-6">
                    <span class="text-sm font-medium">{pageData.category}</span>
                </div>
                <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
                    {pageData.title}
                </h1>
                <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600">{pageData.readTime} • {pageData.publishDate}</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-10">
                <img
                    src={pageData.heroImage}
                    alt="Quantum Computing Readiness"
                    class="rounded-lg shadow-md object-cover h-[400px] w-full sm:h-[500px]"
                />
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Content Section -->
    <section class="bg-gray-50 py-12">
        <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 space-y-16">
            <!-- Introduction -->
            <div>
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">Introduction</h2>
                <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
                    Quantum computing is no longer a theoretical concept—it is a technological frontier that promises to revolutionize industries by solving problems that are currently unsolvable with classical computers. Yet, a staggering 80% of businesses remain unprepared for the quantum leap.
                </p>
                <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
                    This report explores the state of quantum readiness in today's business landscape, highlighting opportunities, challenges, and the steps companies must take to position themselves as leaders in the quantum era.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- The Promise of Quantum Computing -->
            <div>
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">The Promise of Quantum Computing</h2>
                <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
                    Quantum computing operates on principles fundamentally different from classical computing, such as superposition and entanglement. These principles enable quantum computers to process complex computations exponentially faster, opening up unprecedented possibilities in areas like:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-900">Drug Discovery:</strong> Simulating molecular interactions at an atomic level to accelerate pharmaceutical innovation.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-900">Cryptography:</strong> Revolutionizing cybersecurity with unbreakable encryption and new vulnerabilities to classical encryption methods.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-900">Supply Chain Optimization:</strong> Solving combinatorial problems to create hyper-efficient logistics networks.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- The Readiness Gap: Why 80% of Businesses Are Falling Behind -->
            <div>
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">The Readiness Gap: Why 80% of Businesses Are Falling Behind</h2>
                <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
                    Despite its transformative potential, most organizations are not equipped to leverage quantum computing. The primary reasons include:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-900">Limited Understanding:</strong> Many executives lack foundational knowledge about quantum computing and its applications.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-900">Lack of Skilled Talent:</strong> The global talent pool for quantum computing expertise is insufficient to meet demand.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-900">Infrastructure Constraints:</strong> Quantum systems require specialized hardware and environments that are costly and complex to maintain.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- Industries Poised for Quantum Disruption -->
            <div>
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">Industries Poised for Quantum Disruption</h2>
                <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
                    While every industry stands to benefit from quantum advancements, some sectors are particularly ripe for disruption:
                </p>
                <div class="mt-6 space-y-8">
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800">1. Finance</h3>
                        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
                            Quantum algorithms are set to transform risk modeling, portfolio optimization, and fraud detection in financial services.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800">2. Healthcare</h3>
                        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
                            Quantum-enabled simulations will revolutionize personalized medicine and accelerate clinical trials.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800">3. Manufacturing</h3>
                        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
                            Quantum computing will optimize production processes, material design, and quality control, leading to cost savings and innovation.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- How to Prepare Your Business for Quantum Computing -->
            <div>
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">How to Prepare Your Business for Quantum Computing</h2>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-6">
                    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800">1. Educate Your Leadership Team</h3>
                        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
                            Invest in training programs and workshops to ensure your executives and managers understand quantum computing's fundamentals and potential.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800">2. Build Strategic Partnerships</h3>
                        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
                            Collaborate with quantum technology providers, academic institutions, and industry consortia to access expertise and resources.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800">3. Start with Pilot Projects</h3>
                        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
                            Identify specific business challenges that can benefit from quantum solutions and run small-scale pilots to test their feasibility.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800">4. Focus on Quantum-Ready Talent</h3>
                        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
                            Develop an internal quantum team by upskilling employees and recruiting experts with quantum computing backgrounds.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Call to Action -->
    <section class="bg-white py-12">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800">Don't Get Left Behind</h2>
            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600">
                Quantum computing is no longer a distant reality. The decisions you make today will determine your readiness for tomorrow. Let us help you take the first steps toward quantum leadership.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-6 flex justify-center gap-4">
        
                <a href="/insights" class="border border-gray-300 px-6 py-3 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold text-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-100">
                    More Insights
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>
